---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto pt-24 pb-16 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-center px-6 md:px-10">
    <div>
      <p class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-thin">Telling stories throught <span class="font-semibold text-[#F2BE22]">pictures</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-span-2">
      <img src="/img-08.png" alt="Render 3D" class="shadow-lg" />
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="bg-gray-100 py-8">
    <div class="flex justify-center gap-8 lg:gap-30 items-center flex-wrap">
      <img src="/icon-3ds.svg" alt="Render 3D" class="grayscale max-w-[50px]" />
      <img src="/icon-ps.svg" alt="Render 3D" class="grayscale max-w-[50px]" />
      <img src="/icon-ai.svg" alt="Render 3D" class="grayscale max-w-[50px]" />
      <img src="/icon-3ds.svg" alt="Render 3D" class="grayscale max-w-[50px] hidden lg:block" />
      <img src="/icon-ps.svg" alt="Render 3D" class="grayscale max-w-[50px] hidden lg:block" />
      <img src="/icon-ai.svg" alt="Render 3D" class="grayscale max-w-[50px] hidden lg:block" />
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="">
    <div class="max-w-7xl py-16 mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8 items-start px-6 md:px-10">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-gray-700">values</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">method</h3>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
          In every project, I begin with a deep analysis to uncover its unique characteristics and strengths. By understanding these elements, I can tailor the strategy to emphasize and enhance what
          truly matters, ensuring the final result resonates with its essence.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">composition</h3>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
          Each image tells a story. I focus on the composition of the scene as one of the most crucial tools to convey that narrative. By thoughtfully arranging the elements, I create a visual
          experience that speaks volumes, highlighting both form and function.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">lighting</h3>
        <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
          Lighting is a fundamental pillar of my work. It goes beyond illumination—it's about setting the mood, evoking emotions, and creating a captivating atmosphere. With the right balance,
          lighting transforms a simple image into a compelling visual journey.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-gray-100 py-16">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8 items-start px-6 md:px-10">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-gray-700">workflow</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-3 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">Reception of Information</h3>
            <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
              Every project is an opportunity to understand and capture its unique vision. I begin by gathering all relevant information, ensuring that I grasp the full scope and intentions behind the
              project. This step sets the foundation for the entire creative process.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">Base Model Development</h3>
            <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
              I then work on creating the base model, carefully shaping the structure of the scene. This phase focuses on building a solid foundation that allows for the flexibility and creativity
              required to bring the design to life.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">Proposals</h3>
            <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
              Once the base is ready, I explore various creative possibilities. At this stage, I offer visual proposals that align with the client’s vision and project requirements. These proposals
              serve as a guide for refining the direction of the project.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">Production</h3>
            <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
              The production phase is where the magic happens. I fine-tune the textures, details, and lighting to elevate the visual impact of the scene. This is where technical precision and creative
              intuition come together to craft a flawless image.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">Rendering</h3>
            <p class="font-light text-gray-600">
              After all adjustments are made, the rendering process begins. This phase requires patience, as it ensures the final image achieves the highest quality. It's essential to allow adequate
              time for rendering to ensure the best possible outcome.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-8">6. Postproduction</h3>
            <p class="font-light text-gray-600">Last stage of the process. Through image editing programs I work on colors, values and artistic look.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
